 The second edition of the Hon. Tajudeen Ajide/Association of Proprietor of Football Academies of Nigeria (APFAN) will kick off on January 25, 2021. According to APFAN national president, Dr Francis Akinremi, the championship  bankrolled by Ajide, ex-footballer and current executive chairman of Surulere Local Government, to annex soccer talents in the grassroots, will have no fewer than 20 teams competing for the coveted trophy. He noted that all 16 academies that took part in the first edition will also participate in the tournament billed to take place at Abati Barracks, Ojuelegba –Lagos. The teams are defending champions Ify Babes, Fakrem Football Academy, Banjo Football Academy, Puma Football Academy, Sidab Football Academy, Ifraim Football Academy, and Alade Football Academy. Ajide also doubles as the national patron of APFAN. APFAN has showcased U-13, U-15 and U-17 tournaments since 2006. The maiden edition of Late Theophilus Adeyemi Tella Championship was first organised in 2007 while Late Adefemi Olubayo  U-17 Football Tournament was also held in 2011, 2012, and 2013 respectively.